First Support  black owned business! I moved into the area recently and wanted to find a spot where I can go frequently and eat.. I think I found it. Although it was hidden and I seen a line of people and just knew it had to be a chance to take. The food was amazing and the chicken/turkey legs were the best I’ve had. Believe I had the honey garlic chicken leg ? Huge leg and just wished we could add more than 2 sides.
Food is delicious and plenty sometimes alittle pricey but food is great
Not too bad the mac was good. The honey garlic chicken needed more flavor

Moved to NYC 3 weeks ago, this is my favorite place. Food is absolutely delicious, great customer service, delicious fruit drinks. The food is always great. Will be supporting these folks from now on. A must-try for tourists and locals alike.  Thank you so much for everything you do.
I've been here a couple of times. The service is good and the food superb. I recommend the Turkey Wings, mostly because not many places in the area offer them.
Food is pretty good. However, instead of communicating they don't have particular sides I got 3 different orders of mac & cheese when I only ordered one
Can be expensive but it's worth it. Always good foid

Tastes like homemade without the stress. We always get the turkey wings, fried fish, and oxtails with any combo of sides. The food is nicely seasoned without being salty. The meat falls off the bone, but still has texture. They separate the fish from the sides so it stays crisp.  If you order via app, the restaurant will call and offer substitons if something is not available. Love this neighborhood spot.
Southern style dishes. Turkey wings served several different styles
Turkey wings that all I'm going to say 🎉  Spainluc @Instagram
Food is really Good ,Turkey wings ,Lamb chops, mac & cheese collard greens & the Bread pudding  some of my Favorites ❤

This restaurant is surely one of the coolest place in the neighborhood. Always when I visit this place I am highly satisfied. They keep their high  level service and the highest level of food  they offer. You no doubt will love this restaurant. Very  recommended.
Food was good. I use to eat from their truck on 116 Street some years ago. I am glad that they reopened at their restaurant on 142 Street.
Get any of their Turkey wings and prepare to take a nap.
Extremely poor customer service skill from the guy with the white beard
I honestly like their food and customer service, excellent location  to my home. The cashiers are always very friendly. Will visit here again.
THEY ARE THE BESTESSSSS!!!!! Always a family friendly vibe!!

Not only is the food a "more bang for your buck" deal but the customer service here is A+. I ordered some rice with oxtails for my mother and a BBQ rib dinner for myself.  I had a billing issue with one of Uber Eats drivers suddenly canceling my order at the last minute while I was still being charged for the order. I called this restaurant and John, the owner, spoke to me and was very patient and professional. John and his employees went above and beyond to assist me with my issue.  In today's age where many businesses treat you more like a number instead of a human being, it's only right that I commend them for excellent customer service.
Food is great good staff
Turkey wings with Mac and cheese with okra! On point for sure! No seating take-out only prices are low for the amount of good quality food you get! A must go!
Great food and great customer service
The food is amazing the wait staff told me welcome to his home love it so many foods to try dont forget the bread pudding

One of my favorite spots. If you order fried fish or shrimp, they make it fresh. The macaroni and cheese is always good. Garlic honey chicken is bomb. The bbq chicken is bomb. Their homemade punch is delicious. Also, theres a man named Dave there. He is the finest thing on this earth, and half the reason i go. He's in the white shirt. 🥴🤤
It's 👌 ok
Whenever our building don't have hot water Johnny Kaks to the rescue. My family loves his mac n cheese, chicken any favor or turkey wings. We place over 4 family meals and counting.
Try the honey garlic flavor!!!
The food is AMAZING!!! Friendly courteous staff and quick service!
Great real soul food- DELICIOUS- you may have to wait a bit because the venue is small but the wait will be worth it.Seafood is made to order.

I LOVE THEIR FOOD! First 2 times I ordered online, its so good I had to visit the establishment the 3rd time just to get the vibe. The music they had playing let you know all the food was valid 👌🏾 old skool reggae and R&B 😌 I knew I had found my tribe and was home. Even got some cake on the way out 😂

The food is great but they refuse to update inventory on third party sites like seamless and Uber eats. So they call seconds after you booked informing you that they’re out of certain item and tell you what you can replace it with. Terrible! I called and informed the staff of a way to update the inventory online but no one has taken the initiative to do so. Very disappointing because i love the food.

Always busy during mealtimes which we all know is a good sign of great food. Home cooked  taste and feeling to their food. Service is also good, they don't give you that attitude that some of our Caribbean establishments are known for, "Jus sayin' ". No shade, being Caribbean myself I know my peeps. Definitely recommend them and happy to support them with my business.
Food was ok. The decor was dark and it was hot.
Good food for the soul
This place never dissapoints me, consistency is key. Always good food.

Food is decent on most days and I am definitely a fan of their potato salad (whenever available, it reminds me of my mum’s and is definitely a quick fix when she does not make hers).. the service can be a hit or miss depending on who’s serving. I am giving Johnny Kaks two stars because I've gotten sick (stomach pains and vomiting) on more than one occasion after eating their food. Also there was a case where I was overcharged for a meal I usually would pay eight bucks and change for. The lady at the front informed me that their prices had gone up, about two weeks later I ordered the same meal and was charged the regular eight dollars and change I had always paid, I guess everyone has their own prices.
Good Soul Food
Really good soul food, all the time!!!
The portons of food are substantial .  Have avariety of prepared foods. Sevice is friendlh.  Food is good

Boooooooomb jerk chicken!!!!! Gets the clean plate seal of approval!  Call before you go to make sure they're open but if they are just go. Friendly owner and super amazing Johnny Kaks food. Delicious :)

Ok, so when are they going to shut this place down. The customer service is disgusting in here. This is not the same staff from the beginning. These people are rude, lazy and  impatient. The yams and the macaroni n cheese is crazy

Is this food delicious? Yes. Are the prices great for the portion you get? Yes? Then why two stars? BECAUSE THEY HAVE CHICKEN PARTS RULES THAT YOU DON"T KNOW ABOUT UNTIL IT'S TOO LATE. I was disgusted when I ordered two fried chicken meals and all I got were wings. I called and was told "For all chicken dishes, we do not make breast meat. For fried chicken we only make wings, for the other chicken dishes it's legs and thighs". Fine. But you should state your conditions on your menu! On the uber app! Who in their right mind orders fried chicken and expects wings?!

I went in to pick up food for the first time today and the overall experience was great. The staff was kind and approachable. They defenetly looked like a family owned/operated business so it felt really "homie". If you're in the mood for Caribbean and some Soul food, this low key spot is a must try.  The scaffolds kinda hides Johnny Kaks, but its there, don't give up when looking for it. :)
Order for the first time today with UBER EATS. Had  Oxtail,Rice&Peas w Steamed Cabbage and Jerk Turkey Wings, Mac&Cheese w Yams. Very delicious.
Their Food Is Soooo Good, Must Try😀😀😀

This place has gone down hill already. Very rude guy that serves the food. Impatient cashier. Thumbs down all around..

I can’t tell you how the food taste because I never received it. I ordered $35 worth of food for my family and paid for it almost an hour ago. The site said my food order was received and then a few minutes later, was being prepared. I just got a message saying they can’t make my order. How was my food being prepared for at least 30 minutes and now they say they are unable to make it? Are they taking on more orders than they can handle?? More orders than they have food? And why did it take them so long to figure that out? Really. Bad. Business. Practice.

The food is amazing.  But the customer service is horrible. I called my order in a half hour before I arrived to the shop to guarantee I get my food as soon as I arrive. Instead, none of the food I wanted was available and I had to wait almost an hour to get my food. Unacceptable.  Just simply put the food to the side for the customer. And make sure to let a customer know whether or not it's a first come, first serve basis. Smh.
Food is on point !!!!
I order from Here a few times a week Jerk Turkey wings dirty rice with Mac&Cheese. Amazing! Never go wrong ordering from here. Mary!
The food is delicious.
Food is delicious!! My favorite things are the oxtails and mac n cheese.

By far the most nastiest food I’ve had, bake Mac had so much pepper, fried shrimps were  soggy, so was the cat fish🤦🏽‍♀️ Idek if that even cat fish not to mention the canned collard. Most certainly wouldn’t recommend this place.

The food is amazing! I enjoyed every bite! Was a little skeptical because it was my first time trying this restaurant and some of these  soul food restaurants are garbage, so it was a gamble. I came out on top with this one! Definitely ordering again!
Great foods I'm there a lot. Just wish they are open on mondays. But im there every other day

I ordered from Uber eats, BBQ turkey wings, yams, collard greens and dirty rice!! All I have to say I enjoyed every bite of my meal! BBQ turkey wing was nice and tender! Collard greens were the best I ever had in a long time it was fresh and seasoned just right! Candied yams and dirty rice were also delicious!! Dirty rice wasn't as spicy!  Highly recommend!!!!

I ordered from Uber eats, food is AMAZING. i ordered turkey wings with collard greens and Mac n cheese it came with cornbread! Worth every penny. I am from the south this is the first place i found that food has ton of flavor in NY !
That baked Mac & cheese, shrimp & yams is something different💯

I love the food there oh so good. I go during the week and on Sunday. Nice and clean and the people are so nice and friendly. I love the bread pudding. Just saying. Grannycakes64 encourages you to go by and taste some good cooking food.
Everything here is ah-may-ZING! Fish, shrimp, turkey wings, and the baked macaroni and cheese allllll delicious

ive been ordering food for years....... and this is the best meal ive ever had. usually when i order theres always something off..maybe somethings a little too dry, or unseasoned. Not here! the yams tasted like a sunday dinner with my granny, warm and plentiful....the baked macaroni and cheese was actually CHEESY. you'd be surprised how many places forget the actual concept of macaroni and cheese..seriously. and the oxtails were deliciously seasoned, and very juicy fall off the bone. and last but definitely not least - the portions were perfect and proportional. not too much and not too little. it was delivered in less than 30 minutes. im a very happy camper. ill be back again!

Awesome macaroni and an assortment of wonderful cooked with love meals . Oxtails chicken and fish to die for!  $6 meals can't beat it
